    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The raw balsam of the French Maritime pine tree, Pinus pinaster. It is used to produce the distilled "Burgundy turpentine" and "Burgundy pitch," which is not distilled. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047822/MFA Conservation and Art Material Encyclopedia Online: CAMEO (2005-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>De ruwe balsem van de Franse zeeden Pinus pinaster. Wordt gebruikt voor de productie van het gedestilleerde 'Burgundy turpentine' en van 'Burgundy pitch', dat niet is gedestilleerd.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>法國南歐海松（Pinus pinaster）的生香脂。用於製作蒸餾的「勃艮第松節油」（Burgundy turpentine）以及未經蒸餾的「勃艮第樹脂」（Burgundy pitch）。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
